trans-unit.source: Provides the context for an <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.ExpressionBuilder"></xref> object.

An <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ExpressionBuilderContext> object is typically used to obtain a virtual path or a <xref:System.Web.UI.Control.TemplateControl%2A> property for use with an expression builder.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.ExpressionBuilderContext"></xref> class using the specified virtual path.
The virtual path of the file associated with the specified <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.ExpressionBuilder"></xref>.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.ExpressionBuilderContext"></xref> class using the specified template control.
The <xref href="System.Web.UI.TemplateControl"></xref> to use with the specified <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.ExpressionBuilder"></xref>.
Provides an <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.ExpressionBuilder"></xref> object with a reference to a <xref href="System.Web.UI.TemplateControl"></xref> object.
An expression builder might require additional information about the containing page to evaluate or parse the expression value.
This also provides the <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ExpressionBuilder> object with information regarding the page that might be required.
When an instance of a control is part of a control template, the <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ExpressionBuilderContext.TemplateControl%2A> property contains a reference to the containing control.
Returns a virtual path to the file associated with the <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.ExpressionBuilderContext"></xref> object.
The virtual path of the file associated with the <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.ExpressionBuilderContext"></xref>.
